Steps to Create the Script

    Create the File:
        Open your terminal and navigate to the directory where you want to create the file.
        Run the command:

        bash

    touch simple-interest.sh

Edit the File:

    Open the file in your preferred text editor. For example, using nano:

    bash

    nano simple-interest.sh

Add the Script:

    Copy the script provided above and paste it into the file.
    Save and exit the editor (Ctrl+X to exit, Y to confirm changes in nano).

Make the Script Executable:

    Run the command to make the script executable:

    bash

    chmod +x simple-interest.sh

Run the Script:

    Execute the script to verify it works:

    bash

./simple-interest.sh
